								<content:encoded><![CDATA[
<h2>Alex</h2>



<p>Most of the menu is finalized in its appearance and function, and the settings reflect with the game. This was done using TextMeshPro package for Unity.</p>



<ul class="wp-block-gallery columns-2 is-cropped"><li class="blocks-gallery-item"><figure><img src="//joehill27.github.io/2D-Tactical-Web/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Screenshot-8-1024x576.png" alt="" data-id="58" data-link="//joehill27.github.io/2D-Tactical-Web/screenshot-8/" class="wp-image-58" srcset="//joehill27.github.io/2D-Tactical-Web/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Screenshot-8-1024x576.png 1024w, //joehill27.github.io/2D-Tactical-Web/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Screenshot-8-300x169.png 300w, //joehill27.github.io/2D-Tactical-Web/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Screenshot-8-768x432.png 768w, //joehill27.github.io/2D-Tactical-Web/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Screenshot-8-1568x882.png 1568w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure></li><li class="blocks-gallery-item"><figure><img src="//joehill27.github.io/2D-Tactical-Web/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Screenshot-9-1024x576.png" alt="" data-id="57" data-link="//joehill27.github.io/2D-Tactical-Web/screenshot-9/" class="wp-image-57" srcset="//joehill27.github.io/2D-Tactical-Web/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Screenshot-9-1024x576.png 1024w, //joehill27.github.io/2D-Tactical-Web/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Screenshot-9-300x169.png 300w, //joehill27.github.io/2D-Tactical-Web/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Screenshot-9-768x432.png 768w, //joehill27.github.io/2D-Tactical-Web/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Screenshot-9-1568x882.png 1568w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure></li></ul>



<p>To connect the start menu scene and the game scene, Alex wrote a Game Options Menu script that accessed a global variables script and allowed the game scene to create objects based on the options chose in the menu. </p>



<ul class="wp-block-gallery columns-1 is-cropped"><li class="blocks-gallery-item"><figure><img src="//joehill27.github.io/2D-Tactical-Web/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Team-Color-and-Selection-Script-1024x609.png" alt="" data-id="59" data-link="//joehill27.github.io/2D-Tactical-Web/?attachment_id=59" class="wp-image-59" srcset="//joehill27.github.io/2D-Tactical-Web/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Team-Color-and-Selection-Script-1024x609.png 1024w, //joehill27.github.io/2D-Tactical-Web/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Team-Color-and-Selection-Script-300x179.png 300w, //joehill27.github.io/2D-Tactical-Web/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Team-Color-and-Selection-Script-768x457.png 768w, //joehill27.github.io/2D-Tactical-Web/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Team-Color-and-Selection-Script.png 1321w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /><figcaption>Default Team Colors and Keeping Track of Teams and Players</figcaption></figure></li></ul>



<h2>Fernando</h2>



<p>Implemented a Camera Controller that follows the mouse when it goes off screen, and starts a timer to reset the camera back to the player if the mouse is outside of the game screen. The camera can zoom in and out, or scroll horizontally and vertically. The Camera follows locks onto a player when it becomes their turn.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe title="Camera Game Progress" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/364517893?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="640" height="360" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen" allowfullscreen></iframe>
</div></figure>



<h2>Joseph</h2>



<p>Dynamic map generation has been implemented at a basic state, but isn&#8217;t perfect and somethings have to be worked out. In the future the map objects like environment adversaries, and tile sprites will be added based on the map theme and number of players in the game to change the size. </p>



<p>There is a few types of platform types that are randomly generated in different sizes, working from left to right, and increasing in height. Random.Range that is built into Unity is used to generate a random number range that corresponds to one of the block types. The block types are flat platforms, layered platforms, stairs, pyramids, single blocks, and empty space. </p>



<ul class="wp-block-gallery columns-1 is-cropped"><li class="blocks-gallery-item"><figure><img src="//joehill27.github.io/2D-Tactical-Web/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Generate-Base-Platform.png" alt="" data-id="61" data-link="//joehill27.github.io/2D-Tactical-Web/?attachment_id=61" class="wp-image-61" srcset="//joehill27.github.io/2D-Tactical-Web/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Generate-Base-Platform.png 781w, //joehill27.github.io/2D-Tactical-Web/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Generate-Base-Platform-300x257.png 300w, //joehill27.github.io/2D-Tactical-Web/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Generate-Base-Platform-768x658.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 781px) 100vw, 781px" /><figcaption>Method that always creates a base platform</figcaption></figure></li></ul>



<ul class="wp-block-gallery columns-1 is-cropped"><li class="blocks-gallery-item"><figure><img src="//joehill27.github.io/2D-Tactical-Web/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Pick-Block-Type-1024x444.png" alt="" data-id="60" data-link="//joehill27.github.io/2D-Tactical-Web/?attachment_id=60" class="wp-image-60" srcset="//joehill27.github.io/2D-Tactical-Web/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Pick-Block-Type-1024x444.png 1024w, //joehill27.github.io/2D-Tactical-Web/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Pick-Block-Type-300x130.png 300w, //joehill27.github.io/2D-Tactical-Web/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Pick-Block-Type-768x333.png 768w, //joehill27.github.io/2D-Tactical-Web/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Pick-Block-Type.png 1175w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /><figcaption>Subject to change for scaling and using a JSON file, uses methods to create various sized platform types.</figcaption></figure></li></ul>
]]></content:encoded>
